title: For Sale:  Ruger 10/22 with Archangel nomad stock conversion
postcontent:
This is a Ruger 10/22 rifle with a conversion kit made by Archangel to give it a more aggressive look. 

It also comes with the original stock, and it can be returned to its original state, but the sights on the barrel of the 10/22 have been filed down to fit inside the barrel extension of the nomad kit. 

Also, the barrel extension itself must be cut off to be removed, and if that was done, it would not be able to be reapplied. Keep in mind: When this kit is on, the barrel extension must be permanently affixed in order for the overall gun length to reach the legal limit for Oregon.

A base 10/22 goes for like $250, the kit goes for $200. I'm asking about $150 less than it's worth because as it is now I have noticed fairly frequent failures to feed. About one in every 10 shots gets jammed. It may be the cheap .22 ammo that I used, but more likely a piece of the plastic body may be hindering the feeding mechanism from the magazine. The base 10/22 worked fine before the conversion. Let me know if you're interested.

title: For Sale:  LWRC M6 M6A2 Gas Piston 5.56 NATO Carbine
postcontent:
For sale is my LWRC M6A2 Short Stroke Gas Piston 5.56 NATO AR15 Carbine with a Nikon M-223 4-16x40 Sniper Scope.

The M6 is designed and manufactured by Land Warfare Resources Corporation.

It is based on the M4 carbine, with which it shares 80% of its parts.

It features a proprietary short-stroke self-regulating gas piston system and bolt carrier/carrier key design, which prevents trapped gases from contacting the bolt carrier or receiver of the weapon, which reduces the heating and carbon fouling of the internals, simplifies field maintenance, and improves reliability.

All M6A2 Rifles Feature a Match Grade, cold rotary hammer forged barrel with a target crown.

The barrel is treated with NiCorr™ surface conversion technology that extends service life, enhances accuracy, and increases the effective range of the weapon.

The bolt carrier group and the barrel extension of the M6A2 rifle is coated with EXO’s patented nickel-boron surface conversion technology that provides a hard permanent lubrication to the moving parts.

This M6A2 has a low- profile gas block and there is no A-frame front sight to obscure the field of view of the optical device.

It also features a longer mid-length free float rail system with rail covers and a removable return-to-zero top so that any M4 MIL Std 1913 accessory can be mounted to the rail.

The rail has a monolithic profile so you can bridge devices from the receiver to the rail seamlessly and the longer rail also affords more 1913 “real estate” to mount your accessories.

This High-End Rig is Topped with a High-End Nikon M-223 4-16x40 Sniper Scope with BDC.

It also has MOE Magpul Stock and a Magpul MIAD Pistol Grip.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Remington 870 Police Magnum
location: se okc / newalla, Oklahoma City, Oklahoma
postcontent:
18" barrel with magazine extension for a 6+1 capacity. Shoots 2 3/4" and 3" shells. It has rifle sights and I polished the bolt while it was out. This is an actual police gun used by a police department that I bought and completely disassembled and refinished. I replaced the synthetic furniture with wingmaster wood but the original set is included with the gun. This gun was made to work and it functions as it should, you will not find a better gun for home defense. I added a list below of some of the major differences between the police and express guns just to give those of you who dont know why the police versions are more desirable.

The 870 Police has:
 - An aluminum trigger group (vs plastic on the 870 express).
 - Old style magazine retention system (you can add mag extension w/o modification) 
 - The Police gun receives a higher level of inspection and finishing and is built in a special area of the plant from 100% inspected parts.
 - A military-grade parkerized finish.
 - A polished bore.
 - A one piece barrel.
 - A short police-length fore end. 
- The Remington “R3” super recoil pad that reduces felt recoil by 30%.
 - Sling swivels.
 - Heavy-duty magazine spring to ensure positive shell feeding.
 - Heavy-duty trigger-sear spring. to reduce the chance of accidental fire
 - Heavy-duty shell lifter spring which also improves positive feeding.
 - No use of MIM parts, the extractor is milled
 - Police shotguns do not have an ISS (Integrated Safety System) which is a locking mechanism on the safety of commercial shotguns. This type of locking mechanism can cause delay to an officer who needs the weapon but does not have the appropriate key. LE shotguns have the standard, proven, cross bolt safety.
- The receivers used in Police guns are “vibra honed” to smooth out rough finishes and remove burrs before parkerization or bluing.
 - High visibility follower.

title: For Sale:  Training Breaching Door
postcontent:
Further customization can be made to the door upon request by the customer. 

The benefits of using the DSM training breaching door is its ability to quickly reset for continuous breaching, remove the door from the hinges for transportation or service, and change the force required to breach the door. It's intended use is law enforcement breaching training, tactical training, or military enthusiasts.

This technology will allow the door to simulate the effects of breaching 3 classifications of doors using a battering ram or kicking. 

1. Interior Door w/o Dead Bolt (Kicking)
2. Solid Wooden Door w/ Dead Bolt (Battering Ram)
3. Metal or Reinforced Door

The door's materials include 1x2" steel tubing for the structure and a 1/4" steel plate for the striking plate. The frame's materials include 2x3" steel tubing that is braced using 2" angle. 3/4" plywood is screwed to the door frame for aesthetics. The door can be removed from the hinges easily for transportation or service. The whole door assembly has an approximate weight of 350lbs. 

The reusable trigger mechanism is designed similar to a cam system. The "Dead Bolt" will be under spring tension and is required to pass two levels on the guard before breaching. The metal acting as the "Dead Bolt" is made of AR-400 steel. This material is abrasion resistant and will not fail under the abuse of continuous breaching training. 

If you are interested please call or text Holden at 336-899-9sixsix5
